I went to the store this morning to get my usual bagel twist and coffee. The lady on the register who made my coffee was nice and polite. The so called female manager on other hand was rude, nasty, lack manners and very unprofessional. The manager heated up my bagel without wearing gloves after seeing her rubbing her nose and taking something out of her nose with her bear hand. She then put the bagel in a brown bag without wraping it first. This was done again with wearing glove. When I confronted her about it, she was very defensive telling me this is how we do it here. I told her that I come to the store often when I'm around and this is my first time of seen this type of act. She then said to me that she's the manager and she's never seeing me in the store before.  She continued to argue with me while rolling her eyes at me. At some point she rudely asked me if I was still talking. I demanded for my money back  and walked out of the store. I have had other complained about the manager and poor customer service, but I continued to go there because I've never experienced it. After today, I will no longer be going there until that manger is changed, and I will make sure I spread the word around.
